SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 17
BY SENATOR HODGES
COMMENDATIONS. Commends Brooklyn Antoinette Kersey on being selected as the
"Student of the Year" at Doyle High School in Livingston Parish.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend and congratulate Brooklyn Antoinette Kersey on being selected as the 2025-
3 2026 "Student of the Year" at Doyle High School in Livingston Parish.
4 WHEREAS, Brooklyn Antoinette Kersey has been named the 2025-2026 "Student
5 of the Year" at Doyle High School, an honor reflecting her outstanding dedication to
6 scholarship, leadership, and character; and
7 WHEREAS, Brooklyn Antoinette Kersey has achieved notable academic success,
8 maintaining an impressive 4.2 grade point average and earning an ACT score of 28, and
9 demonstrating discipline and commitment to excellence in the classroom; and
10 WHEREAS, Brooklyn is the daughter of Brian and Brittany Kersey, who have
11 supported and encouraged her academic, athletic, and personal accomplishments; and
12 WHEREAS, Brooklyn has distinguished herself as a student-athlete, having played
13 competitive softball for ten years, including five years as a member of the Doyle Lady Tigers
14 softball team, and she has also competed as a powerlifter for Doyle High School's
15 powerlifting team for three years; and
16 WHEREAS, Brooklyn has demonstrated exemplary leadership through active
17 involvement in numerous student organizations, serving as 4-H president, Beta Club
18 vice-president, financial manager for the SADD Club, and as a dedicated member of the
