1 school's Future Farmers of America (FFA) Club; and
2 WHEREAS, Brooklyn was further honored by her peers when she was crowned
3 Doyle High School's 2025-2026 Homecoming Queen, recognizing her leadership, integrity,
4 and positive influence within the school community; and
5 WHEREAS, Brooklyn is committed to service and personal growth, enjoying
6 opportunities to give back to her community, pursue outdoor activities, explore new
7 interests, and prepare for her future endeavors; and
8 WHEREAS, Brooklyn plans to attend Louisiana State University to earn a bachelor's
9 degree in human movement sciences, and thereafter transfer to Louisiana State University-
10 New Orleans to pursue a degree in occupational therapy, reflecting her desire to serve others
11 through a meaningful healthcare profession.
12 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
13 does hereby commend and congratulate Brooklyn Antoinette Kersey on being selected as
14 the 2025-2026 "Student of the Year" at Doyle High School in Livingston Parish.
15 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to
16 Brooklyn Antoinette Kersey.
